# Commit Message Rules

## Format

- Use exactly: `<type> <description>`
- Allowed types: `[FEAT]`, `[FIX]`, `[DOCS]`, `[STYLE]`, `[REFACTOR]`, `[TEST]`, `[CHORE]`
- Keep the description at 50 characters or fewer
- Start the description with an uppercase letter
- Do not end the description with a period
- Use imperative mood
- Be specific and concise

## Examples

```text
Good:
[FEAT] Add user authentication
[FIX] Resolve memory leak in parser
[DOCS] Update installation guide

Bad:
[FEAT] Added a new feature for user authentication with JWT tokens
Fixed stuff
refactor: Refactored the code
```

## Commit Practices

- Commit in small, logical chunks
- Keep one concern per commit
- Test changes before committing
- Do not create WIP commits; use stash instead
